name: Donald Trump
summary: As the US election nears, polls indicate a tight race between Donald Trump and Kamala Harris. CBS News reports that different information sources and beliefs are shaping the campaign, while NBC News finds the candidates in a "dead heat." Harris has granted an interview to Fox News and visited Pennsylvania, where Trump has also been campaigning. Economic concerns and divided opinions on key issues contribute to the close contest, as highlighted by ABC News. Sky News describes the race as a "dead heat" and reports on an incident involving former President Bill Clinton. The BBC focuses on Harris's demands for Trump's medical records, while the Financial Times examines the candidates' efforts to sway Latino voters. Trump has criticized a biopic about his business reality show, The Apprentice, while pledging to eliminate double taxation for expat Americans, as reported by The Guardian US and Financial Times, respectively.

summary: Brian Stanley, a former Sinn Féin TD, has been removed as committee lead due to an allegation of gross misconduct. The party has referred the matter to the gardaí (Irish police).
